item.title: CVE-2018-0741|2024-08-05T03:35:49.304Z -- microsoft%20corporation -- color%20management%20module%20%28icm32.dll%29
item.description: The Color Management Module (Icm32.dll) in Windows 7 SP1 and Windows Server 2008 SP2 and R2 SP1 allows an information disclosure vulnerability due to the way objects are handled in memory, aka "Microsoft Color Management Information Disclosure Vulnerability".
